  "prompt": "Which is a good refrence book for Servlets and JSP?",
  "response": "A highly recommended reference book for Servlets and JSP is:\n\n**\"Head First Servlets and JSP\" by Bryan Basham, Kathy Sierra, and Bert Bates**\n\nThis book is well-received for its engaging, visual approach to learning, making complex concepts more accessible. It covers Servlets and JSP in detail, along with best practices, examples, and exercises.\n\nOther notable references include:\n\n1. **\"Java Servlet Programming\" by Jason Hunter and William Crawford** - This book provides a comprehensive overview of Servlet technology and covers practical examples and thoroughly explains the API.\n\n2. **\"Core Servlets and JavaServer Pages\" by Marty Hall and Larry Brown** - A detailed introduction to Servlet and JSP technology, along with a wealth of practical examples.\n\n3. **\"Java EE 8 Application Development\" by Carl Dea, et al.** - While broader, this book covers the use of JSP and Servlets as part of Java EE applications, making it a good resource for modern development techniques.\n\nAny of these books would be a great starting point or reference for learning about Servlets and JSP!",
